<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Risk Managers develop a deep subject matter expertise in the Global Markets, and as trusted advisors to the various trading & sales business lines, engage in active dialogue with the risk takers to fully articulate the nature of the risk and provide transparency of risk to senior management. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
The Markets Risk Intern Program is designed to develop and coach analytical and quantitative talent to be deployed in the Global Markets Risk (GMR) organization.
</p>
<ul class="bac">
<li>Gain hands-on, in-depth experience applying quantitative knowledge to specific financial challenges</li>
<li>Participate in a variety of activities within GMR, Global Risk, and bank-wide, designed to foster teamwork, encourage networking, and demonstrate Bank of America’s vision and culture</li>
<li>The Markets Risk Intern Program is meant to be a feeder pool for strong performers into the full time Markets Risk Analyst Program</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">The Markets Risk Intern Program is seeking a combination of academic aptitude and quantitative skills including:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Pursuing an undergraduate degree in quantitative disciplines such as engineering, mathematics, statistics, computer science, quantitative finance, economics, and/or business</li>
	<li>Strategic and creative thinking ability</li>
	<li>Exceptional communication skills</li>
	<li>Demonstrate leadership, initiative, and resourcefulness in school, community, or work experience</li>
	<li>Strong work ethic, ability to multi-task, and teamwork orientation</li>
	<li>Dedicated to building a career in financial services</li>
	<li>Minimum GPA of 3.3 </li>
	<li>Must have eligibility to work in the U.S.</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">The Markets Risk Intern Program allows interns to gain practical experience in Global Markets Risk while also participating in enterprise-wide and line of business intern events.<br /><br />The intern experience includes: </p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Orientation to Bank of America</li>
	<li>Mid-point learning and networking event </li>
	<li>Line of business specific events</li>
	<li>Team Bank of America community involvement</li>
	<li>Performance  coaching and feedback</li>
	<li>Business & compliance training</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">Associate development is critical to the success of Global Markets Risk and Bank of America in general.  Executive leadership within the organization is committed to the success of our young associates.  As a result, the internship experience is designed to offer a view into the company, culture and Global Markets Risk organization.</p>
